First, I think you have too many parentheses here. Can you trim out the redundant pair?

Second, you can't dereference `event_message_global_enable` before you're sure it was correctly extracted. It may not have been initialised by the caller, in which case a read here with a failure to extract the data will cause undefined behaviour (read of uninitialised memory). You should do the following:

```
...
rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract_p(buf, event_message_global_enable);
if (rc) {
    return rc;
}
...
if (*event_message_global_enable == ...) {
```

This is dangerous (as you're passing a signed value to an unsigned type for the buffer size), unnecessary (as the msgbuf design already handles what you're trying to do) and incorrect (as you've lost any overflow information for the extractions so far).

The `pldm_msgbuf_extract_p()` below is enough.

```
if (*event_message_global_enable == PLDM_EVENT_MESSAGE_GLOBAL_ENABLE_ASYNC_KEEP_ALIVE) {
    pldm_msgbuf_extract_p(buf, hearbeat_timer);
}

...
```
